# Main/State.elm — EARLY

Pure-types leaf module for the Elm client. Owns the `Model`
shape, every supporting data type the rest of the app needs to
pattern-match on, and the initial Model (`baseModel`). No I/O,
no rendering, no Msg, no update logic.

## Status

- **Label:** EARLY. Dependency leaf: other Main.* modules
  import from here; nothing Main-side imports back in.

## Exports

Types:

- `Model` — the full client state. Two field groups visibly
  commented: game-state (`board`, `hands`, `scores`,
  `activePlayerIndex`, `turnIndex`, `deck`,
  `cardsPlayedThisTurn`, `victorAwarded`,
  `turnStartBoardScore`) and UI-layer (`drag`, `sessionId`,
  `status`, `score`, `hintedCards`, `popup`, `actionLog`,
  `replay`, `replayBaseline`, `replayBoardRect`).
  - `replayBoardRect : Maybe { x, y }` — populated via
    `Browser.Dom.getElement` at replay start. Live viewport
    offset of the 800×600 board div. Used by the replay
    synthesizer to translate board-frame coords into current
    viewport coords. Nothing outside replay.

- `AwaitingHandRect { action, source }` — intermediate
  replay state while waiting on a `Browser.Dom.getElement`
  for a hand card's live viewport rect. Transitions to
  `Animating` on `HandCardRectReceived`. Typically one frame.
- `ReplayProgress` — `{ step, paused }`. Walker over
  `actionLog` (a `List ActionLogEntry`), advanced on every
  `onAnimationFrame` tick via the FSM in `Game.Replay.Time`;
  `step` is the index of the NEXT entry to apply;
  `paused = True` halts ticks.
- `PopupContent` — `{ admin, body }`. Turn-ceremony popup.
- `StatusMessage` / `StatusKind` — `Inform` / `Celebrate` /
  `Scold`. Drives the status bar text + colour.
- `ActionOutcome` — `{ model : Model, status : StatusMessage }`.
  The return type of `Main.Apply.applyAction`: the post-action
  Model plus the message describing what happened, generated
  at the point of mutation. Lets callers choose whether to
  apply the outcome's status (human actions do; replay keeps
  its own "Replaying…" and ignores).
- `DragState` — `NotDragging | Dragging DragInfo`.
- `DragInfo` — source, cursor, originalCursor, floaterTopLeft,
  wings, hoveredWing, boardRect, clickIntent, gesturePath,
  pathFrame. `floaterTopLeft` is the render-canonical field;
  see the inline doc on the type itself in `State.elm`.
- `DragSource` — `FromBoardStack CardStack | FromHandCard Card`.
  Content-based, matching the wire format.
- `PathFrame` — `BoardFrame | ViewportFrame`. Determines which
  DOM parent the drag floater renders under: `BoardFrame`
  renders as a board-div child (CSS handles board→viewport
  translation); `ViewportFrame` renders at the top level with
  `position: fixed`. Python emits `BoardFrame` for intra-board
  synthesized paths; hand-origin drags (Elm captures + replay
  synthesizes) use `ViewportFrame` because they cross the
  board widget boundary.
- `Point` — `{ x, y }`.
- `GesturePoint` — `{ tMs, x, y }`. Behaviorist telemetry
  sample captured per `MouseMove` during a drag; the whole
  list is POSTed alongside the resulting WireAction as
  `gesture_metadata`. `tMs` is the `MouseEvent.timeStamp`
  (performance.now-style, document-lifetime relative,
  fractional ms).
- `Flags` — `{ initialSessionId : Maybe Int }`. HTML harness
  input.
- `RemoteState` — shape used for the bundle's `initialState`
  (see `ActionLogBundle`) and for `model.replayBaseline` (the
  Instant Replay rewind target).
- `ActionLogBundle` — `{ initialState, actions }`. The
  `/sessions/:id/actions` response body. Bootstrap fold:
  `initialState` seeds the Model; `actions` is threaded
  through `Main.Apply.applyAction` to reach current state.
- `CompleteTurnOutcome` lives in `Game.Game`, not here.

Helpers + constants:

- `activeHand : Model -> Hand` — hands[activePlayerIndex],
  falling back to Hand.empty on out-of-range.
- `setActiveHand : Hand -> Model -> Model` — replaces
  hands[activePlayerIndex] with the given Hand.
- `boardDomIdFor : String -> String` — per-gameId board
  DOM id (`"lynrummy-board-" ++ gameId`). Used by
  `Browser.Dom.getElement` on drag start and at replay
  start. Per-instance so multiple Play instances on one
  page (BOARD_LAB) don't collide.
- `baseModel : Model` — initial Model; defaults to hardcoded
  Dealer opening board + canned P1 hand + empty P2 hand.

## Invariants

- `hands` length equals the number of seats (2 for LynRummy).
- `scores` length matches `hands` length.
- `activePlayerIndex` is a valid index into both lists (0 or 1
  in practice).
- `turnIndex` starts at 0, monotonically increases.
- `deck`, `cardsPlayedThisTurn`, `victorAwarded`,
  `turnStartBoardScore` are the `GameState` fields
  `Game.applyCompleteTurn` reads + writes. Layout matches
  `Game.Game.GameState`'s extensible record shape.
- `baseModel`'s game-state fields are fine for a new session;
  they get overwritten on session resume by
  `bootstrapFromBundle` — seed from `ActionLogBundle.initialState`
  then fold the bundle's actions through the local reducer.

## What this module deliberately does NOT expose

- `Msg` — lives in `Main.elm` (app bootstrap).
- Decoders for the response-shape types — live in
  `Main.Wire`.
- `Model`-mutating logic beyond setActiveHand — lives in
  `Main.Apply` or in per-handler code in `Main.elm`.
- Any Html/view code — lives in `Main.View`.

## Dependencies

Imports only `Game.*` primitives: `Card`, `CardStack`,
`GestureArbitration` (for Rect), `Hand`, `PlayerTurn` (for
CompleteTurnResult), `Score` (for forStacks), `WingOracle`
(for WingId), `WireAction`, `Dealer` (for hardcoded baseModel
board/hand fallbacks).

No dependency on any other Main.* module.
